Output 1: 
1.1. Local Development projects were selected and initiated in all 9 Governorates, where by in the South cluster - Basra, Missan , ThiQar- with support of RPAs, North cluster directly implemented by the Governorates of Dohuk, Erbil and Suly and the Central cluster - Anbar, Nenewah and Salahdin- in partnership with UN Habitat. About 40 representatives of local and international NGOs, CSOs, universities, officials, businesses and women groups capacitated on strategic communications and visibility through multiple online training sessions. 
1.2. European Municipalities were selected to peer with all 9 Iraqi Governorates, most project activities agreed and contracts pending signature. Civil Society Component: 89 applications were received and are currently under evaluation. 
New activity: Lets Beat Corona awareness campaign on COVID 19: Awareness raised among an estimated 17.8 million people online and offline from June to September 2020: 30,000 awareness items disseminated in 2960 hospitals, neighborhoods and public places, nearly 1.4 million people reached through social media. --- 35 youth from the southern governorates become Community Reporters after completing the on-campus and online training on broadcast and photo journalism during 2019-2020. They have been engaged in and contracted to cover nearly 35 UNDP activities. 

Output 3.1: Damaged houses, public facilities rehabilitated in post-conflict areas, in line with the 2018 PRPs. 
3.1.1.: 111 individual houses weather-proofed / repaired / rehabilitated, including WASH facilities with the support of this Action in Mosul, Heet and Yathrib and over 60 houses on-going; 
3.1.2.: Two public facilities rehabilitated with the support of this Action - incl. an emergency clinic in Yathrib and a school in Heet, retrofitted using passive design solutions and environmentally-friendly and locally-sourced construction materials; 
3.1.3. 400 households connected to improved potable water infrastructure in Yathrib with the support of this Action, with over 100 children taking part to an Health & Hygiene Awareness Raising Campaign and Child Accident Prevention Campaign - both of which were held in Yathrib; and 13,000 people benefiting from the rehabilitation of a 4,3 km-long irrigation canal serving 18,000 acres of agricultural land in Yathrib; emergency flood intervention conducted in the area of Maghreb in Mosul; 
3.1.4. Two newly landscaped multi-functional public spaces created with the support of this Action in Heet and Yathrib and one (of 67,000 sqm) under rehabilitation in Mosul (incl. 6 new sports facilities for youth); over 550 new trees and plants planted in the new parks; 
3.1.5.: Over 25 youth engaged in projects’ design and implementation with the support of this Action (100% male) and some 500 athletes participated to 3 sports festivals held in the 3 cities

Output 3.2.: On-the-job vocational training delivered and jobs for youth created in line with greener and safer construction technologies. 
3.2.1. over 700 jobs created in target areas; 30 unemployed and disadvantaged women enrolled in horticultural training courses and employed in Yarmouk Park, Mosul; 
3.2.2.: 3,500 workman/days for skilled and unskilled labourers; 
3.2.3. Zero; 
3.2.4.: Three iterations of 2-day Green Building Training delivered in Mosul, Heet and Yathrib to a total of 42 public officials; 
3.2.5.: None; 
3.2.6.: None.

Output 1: 
1.1. Steering committee was held to approve the Work plan and and endorse the local development projects deriving from the Provincial Strategies and selected by evaluation panels . 
1.2. Procurement and contractual procedures were launched in all 9 Governorates and Interagency agreement for partnership between UNDP and Un Habitat for Anbar, Nenewah and Salahdin local projects was signed. 
1.3. Open call for Expression of Interest was advertised to atract European Municipalities to peer with Iraqi Governorates. 1.4 35 Community Reporters were trained on-campus in 2019, on broadcast and photo-journalism.

